<s:slide id="philosophy" status="ready">
<s:title>ASF philosophy</s:title>
<s:content>
<p>
<ol>
  <li>Collaborative software development</li>
  <li>Commercial-friendly standard license</li>
  <li>Consistently high quality software</li>
  <li>Respectful, honest, technical-based interaction</li>
  <li>Faithful implementation of standards</li>
  <li>Security as a mandatory feature</li>
</ol>
</p>
</s:content>
</s:slide>

<s:slide id="classical" status="ready">
<s:title>"Classical" FOSS project/community</s:title>
<s:content>
<p>
<ol>
  <li>One person has a need and starts a project</li>
  <li>People start to contribute</li>
  <li>People get involved with decisions</li>
  <li>The original creator is having new interests or is getting bored (leaving the room)</li>
</ol>
</p>
</s:content>
</s:slide>

